ZH: 我已经获得了足够的学分，可以毕业了。
EN: I have accumulated enough credits to graduate.

ZH: 这门课程值5个学分。
EN: This course is worth 5 credits.

ZH: 我每学期至少要修满15个学分。
EN: I have to complete at least 15 credits per semester.

ZH: 学分可以用来申请奖学金。
EN: Credits can be used to apply for scholarships.

ZH: 在这个专业里，你需要至少30个学分才能毕业。
EN: In this major, you need at least 30 credits to graduate.

ZH: 我转学的时候，只有一半的课程能转移学分。
EN: When I transferred schools, only half of my courses were transferable for credits.

ZH: 你必须达到一定的学分才能晋升到下一个年级。
EN: You must achieve a certain number of credits to move up to the next grade.

ZH: 我做了很多额外工作，以便获得额外的学分。
EN: I did a lot of extra work in order to earn extra credits.

ZH: 这门课程需要预修一个先修课程，否则不能得到学分。
EN: This course requires a prerequisite course to be taken before getting any credits.

ZH: 学生可以通过考试获得学分，而无需上课。
EN: Students can earn credits through exams without attending classes.

ZH: 学分是衡量学生学术成绩的一个重要指标。
EN: Credits are an important indicator of students' academic performance.

ZH: 我要花很多时间来努力获得足够的学分。
EN: I will have to spend a lot of time working hard to earn enough credits.

ZH: 学分需要在一定期限内完成，否则将失效。
EN: Credits must be completed within a certain time frame, or they will expire.

ZH: 这门课程涵盖了从基础到高级学分的知识。
EN: This course covers knowledge from basic to advanced credits.

ZH: 学分的认可有时会因为学校的政策而变化。
EN: Credit recognition can sometimes change due to school policies.

ZH: 这个项目分为必修和选修学分。
EN: This program is divided into required and elective credits.

ZH: 大部分学生每学期至少要修满12个学分。
EN: Most students have to complete at least 12 credits per semester.

ZH: 学分转移的过程相对简单，只需要几个步骤即可完成。
EN: The process of transferring credits is relatively simple and can be completed in a few steps.

ZH: 学生们可以根据自己的兴趣选择修满学分的课程。
EN: Students can choose courses to complete credits based on their interests.

ZH: 学分可以在不同的学校之间转移，前提是学校有合作协议。
EN: Credits can be transferred between different schools, provided that there is a cooperation agreement between the schools.
